{"content":"---\ntitle: \"XSLT Extension Objects\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.technology: dotnet-standard\nms.assetid: a4ebdbad-087c-4cfe-acc0-17c48142f81a\nauthor: \"mairaw\"\nms.author: \"mairaw\"\n---\n# XSLT Extension Objects\nExtension objects are used to extend the functionality of style sheets. Extension objects are maintained by the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList> class.  \n  \n The following are advantages to using an extension object rather than embedded script:  \n  \n-   Provides better encapsulation and reuse of classes.  \n  \n-   Allows style sheets to be smaller and more maintainable.  \n  \n XSLT extension objects are added to the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList> object using the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList.AddExtensionObject%2A> method. A qualified name and namespace URI are associated with the extension object at that time.  \n  \n> [!NOTE]\n>  The FullTrust permission set is required to call the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList.AddExtensionObject%2A> method. For more information, see [Code Access Security](../../../../docs/framework/misc/code-access-security.md) and [Named Permission Sets](https://docs.microsoft.com/previous-versions/dotnet/netframework-4.0/4652tyx7(v=vs.100)).  \n  \n The data types returned from extension objects are one of the four basic XPath data types of `number`, `string`, `Boolean`, and `node set`.  \n  \n Any method that is defined with the `params` keyword, which allows an unspecified number of parameters to be passed, is not currently supported by the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XslCompiledTransform> class. XSLT style sheets that utilize any method defined with the `params` keyword will not work correctly. For details, see [params](~/docs/csharp/language-reference/keywords/params.md).  \n  \n### To use an XSLT extension object  \n  \n1.  Create an <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList> object and add the extension object using <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList.AddExtensionObject%2A> method.  \n  \n2.  Call the extension object from the style sheet.  \n  \n3.  Pass the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList> object to the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XslCompiledTransform.Transform%2A> method.  \n  \n## See also\n\n- [XSLT Transformations](../../../../docs/standard/data/xml/xslt-transformations.md)\n- [XSLT Security Considerations](../../../../docs/standard/data/xml/xslt-security-considerations.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,174],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"XSLT Extension Objects\"\nms.date: \"03/30/2017\"\nms.technology: dotnet-standard\nms.assetid: a4ebdbad-087c-4cfe-acc0-17c48142f81a\nauthor: \"mairaw\"\nms.author: \"mairaw\"","nodes":[{"content":"XSLT Extension Objects","nodes":[{"pos":[0,22],"content":"XSLT Extension Objects","nodes":[{"content":"XSLT Extension Objects","pos":[0,22]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[181,203],"content":"XSLT Extension Objects","linkify":"XSLT Extension Objects","nodes":[{"content":"XSLT Extension Objects","pos":[0,22]}]},{"content":"Extension objects are used to extend the functionality of style sheets.","pos":[204,275]},{"content":"Extension objects are maintained by the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList&gt;</ph> class.","pos":[276,361],"source":" Extension objects are maintained by the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList> class."},{"content":"The following are advantages to using an extension object rather than embedded script:","pos":[368,454]},{"content":"Provides better encapsulation and reuse of classes.","pos":[464,515]},{"content":"Allows style sheets to be smaller and more maintainable.","pos":[525,581]},{"content":"XSLT extension objects are added to the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList&gt;</ph> object using the <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList.AddExtensionObject%2A&gt;</ph> method.","pos":[588,752],"source":"XSLT extension objects are added to the <xref:System.Xml.Xsl.XsltArgumentList> object using the